@after
title: Independence won!
subtitle: ... what now?
view-if: consultation_yes_pc > consultation_no_pc
on-arrival: {!
    Q.countdows.push("unio_breakup");
    Q.countdows.push("jxsi_formation");
    Q.unio_breakup_countdown = 5;
    Q.jxsi_formation_countdown = 6;
    Q.plebiscite_election_countdown = 3;
!}

After the celebration, it is clear what the question on everyone's mind right is: what now? A non-binding consultation does not force the Generalitat into any path of action, and it is not like the current [+ cat_coalition_disp +] has made any provisions for continuing any path towards independence after this. It may be time to re-think any roadmaps towards independence...

- @post_event: Was everything just for this?

@after_no
title: This is no short of unexpected...
on-arrival: {!
    if (!Q.achievement_majoria_no_silenciosa) {
        window.achievementNotif('Majoria No Silenciosa', 'img/achievements/majoria_silenciosa.jpg', 5);
    }
    this.achieve("majoria_no_sileciosa");

    Q.independence_movement -= 30;
    Q.independence_trust -= 30;
    Q.cat_spa_relations += 25;

    Q.countdowns.push("parlament_snap_election");
    Q.parlament_snap_election_countdown = 1;

    // TODO: ramifications of what happens here besides the snap election, specially for CiU. It's virutally impossible to get to this scene though.
!}
view-if: consultation_yes_pc <= consultation_no_pc

This never-expected result has certainly caught everyone off-guard. [? if president_gender = "m": President ?][? if president_gender = "f": Presidenta ?][+ president +] is under heavy pressure now, with voices from all the Parlament's spectrum, including their own party, to hold elections. As for us, the future is as blurry as it can get. This may very well be the end of the independence movement for this generation.

- @post_event: Was everything just for this?
